The paper deals with algorithms for handling massive graphs, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of the clustering algorithm to graph partitioning, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also presents algorithms for solving linear systems and approximating eigenvalues, which fall under the categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the design of local algorithms, which could also fall under the category of Computational Geometry (cs.CG).
